MDC Partners Inc. Key Developments

MDC Partners Inc. Presents at Fourth Annual Bernstein Future of Media Summit, Jun-28-2017 09:30 AM
Jun 22 17
MDC Partners Inc. Presents at Fourth Annual Bernstein Future of Media Summit, Jun-28-2017 09:30 AM. Venue: Hyatt Centric Times Square hotel, New York City, New York, United States. Speakers: David B. Doft, Chief Financial Officer.


MDC Partners Inc. Presents at 45th Annual J.P. Morgan Global Technology, Media and Telecom Conference, May-24-2017 08:40 AM
May 17 17
MDC Partners Inc. Presents at 45th Annual J.P. Morgan Global Technology, Media and Telecom Conference, May-24-2017 08:40 AM. Venue: Westin Copley Place, 10 Huntington Ave., Boston, Massachusetts, United States. Speakers: David B. Doft, Chief Financial Officer, Scott L. Kauffman, Chairman and Chief Executive Officer.


MDC Partners Inc. Announces Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the First Quarter Ended March 31, 2017; Provides Earnings Guidance for the Full Year of 2017
Apr 27 17
MDC Partners Inc. announced unaudited consolidated earnings results for the first quarter ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported revenue of $344,700,000 compared to $309,042,000 a year ago. Operating profit was $8,399,000 compared to $8,548,000 a year ago. Loss before income taxes and equity in earnings of non-consolidated affiliates was $5,575,000 compared to $24,635,000 a year ago. Net loss was $9,683,000 compared to $22,434,000 a year ago. Net loss attributable to the company was $10,566,000 compared to $23,293,000 a year ago. Net loss attributable to the company common shareholders was $11,073,000 or $0.21 per basic and diluted share compared to $23,293,000 or $0.47 per basic and diluted share a year ago. Adjusted EBITDA was $35,813,000 compared to $32,819,000 a year ago. Net cash used in operating activities was $30,676,000 compared to $122,416,000 a year ago.

The company provided earnings guidance for the full year of 2017. For the year, the company’s expects organic revenue approximately 4% growth and adjusted EBITDA margin approximately 100 basis points increase.


